  "local_port": 40882,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I use WhatsApp with a different number than the cell phone I have it installed in without changing sims just adding the other number?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use WhatsApp with a different number than the one currently registered on your phone without changing SIM cards. WhatsApp allows you to add a second phone number by using the **Linked Devices** feature or the **WhatsApp Companion Mode** (only for Android devices). Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### 1. **Using WhatsApp Companion Mode (Android Only)**  \nThis feature allows you to use two different WhatsApp accounts on the same phone:\n   1. Open WhatsApp and go to **Settings**.\n   2. Tap on your profile icon (top-right corner).\n   3. Select **Add Account**.\n   4. Enter the new phone number you want to use and verify it.\n   5. You can now switch between the two accounts easily from the **More Options** menu (three dots).\n\n### 2. **Using Linked Devices (Multi-Device Feature)**  \nIf you don\u2019t want to use Companion Mode, you can link another device to your primary WhatsApp account. For example:\n   1. Install WhatsApp on a secondary device (like a tablet, another phone, or a computer).\n   2. Open WhatsApp on that device and select **Link to Existing Account**.\n   3. Scan the QR code using your primary phone\u2019s WhatsApp settings (**Settings > Linked Devices**).\n   4. The secondary device will now use the same account as your primary phone.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- You cannot use two different numbers on the same WhatsApp installation simultaneously without using Companion Mode (Android) or a multi-device setup.\n- If you want to switch the number associated with your current WhatsApp account, you\u2019ll need to verify the new number and migrate your account (which will disconnect the old number).\n- WhatsApp\u2019s Companion Mode is currently only available for Android devices. iOS users cannot use two accounts on the same phone.\n\nBy using these methods, you can effectively use WhatsApp with a different number without changing your SIM card.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
